You have successfully created an Atlassian Plugin!

Here are the SDK commands you'll use immediately:

* atlas-run   -- installs this plugin into the product and starts it on localhost
* atlas-debug -- same as atlas-run, but allows a debugger to attach at port 5005
* atlas-cli   -- after atlas-run or atlas-debug, opens a Maven command line window:
                 - 'pi' reinstalls the plugin into the running product instance
* atlas-help  -- prints description for all commands in the SDK

Full documentation is always available at:

https://developer.atlassian.com/display/DOCS/Introduction+to+the+Atlassian+Plugin+SDK

Development setup:
IntelliJ recommended:
1. Install Atlassian Plugin SDK: (Windows url) - https://developer.atlassian.com/server/framework/atlassian-sdk/install-the-atlassian-sdk-on-a-windows-system/

2. Generate the swagger-codegen-codedx-api-client with the following command:
java -jar .\swagger-codegen-cli-2.3.1.jar generate -i C:\Users\youruser\Source\Repos\codedx\dev\lift-project\swaggerUI\src\static\swagger.json
--api-package com.avi.codedx.client.api --model-package com.avi.codedx.client.api --group-id com.avi.codedx --artifact-
id swagger-codegen-codedx-api-client -l java -o swagger-codegen-codedx-api --library jersey2

3. Install the swagger-codegen-codedx-api-client into your local maven repository by running the following command in the swagger-codegen-codedx-api/ directory: atlas-mvn install

4. Import pom.xml using IntelliJ

5. Point IntelliJ to the Maven version installed to the Atlassian plugin SDK: File -> Settings -> Build, Execution, Deployment -> Build Tools -> Maven -> Maven home directory. Default installation of the plugin SDK is in C:\Applications\Atlassian


To run the built plugin in an instance of bamboo, run the bamboo:run maven task.

The plugin can be configured with QuickReload in the codedx-bamboo-plugin POM file. If this is set to true, a developer only needs to run bamboo:run,
and then run atlas-mvn package in a seperate console session to build an updated version of the plugin, and have the Bamboo instance automatically reload the plugin.

When setting up bamboo, don't forget to configure your git install directory via the Server capabilities administration menu.

To debug in Intellij: run bamboo:debug, then go to Run->Attach to local process... and select the Catalina process.